class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLastWord(String s) {
        // Step 1: Trimspaces from both sides
        s = s.trim();
        // Step 2: Split String into words using spaces
        String[] words = s.split("\\s+");

        //Step 3: Get the last word's length
        return words[words.length -1].length();
    }

}

Explaination:

🚀 Algorithm:
🛠️ Step 1: Trim Trailing Spaces
Remove extra spaces at the end using trim() to handle cases like " Hello World ".
🛠️ Step 2: Split the String into Words
Use split("\\s+") to split words based on spaces.
🛠️ Step 3: Get the Last Word's Length
Take the last word from the split array and return its length.
